ans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Travisse had at least 1 son with William Travisse."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1576–Male":"1576–Surnud","1596–1664":"1596–1664","–Female":"Surnud","1596 estimate":"1596","1664":"1664","1576":"1576","1596":"1596","Wigan, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Wigan, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1576–Male":"1576–Kuollut","1596–1664":"1596–1664","–Female":"Kuollut","1596 estimate":"1596","1664":"1664","1576":"1576","1596":"1596","Wigan, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Wigan, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1576–Male":"1576–Décédé","1596–1664":"1596–1664","–Female":"Décédée","1596 estimate":"1596","1664":"1664","1576":"1576","1596":"1596","Wigan, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Wigan, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Travisse a eu au moins 1 fils avec William Travisse."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1576–Male":"1576–Verstorben","1596–1664":"1596–1664","–Female":"Verstorben","1596 estimate":"1596","1664":"1664","1576":"1576","1596":"1596","Wigan, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Wigan, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Travisse hatte mit William Travisse mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1576–Male":"1576–Desede","1596–1664":"1596–1664","–Female":"Desede","1596 estimate":"1596","1664":"1664","1576":"1576","1596":"1596","Wigan, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Wigan, Lancashire, Angletè, United 